    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Neglected Commuters</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert Watson letter, prompted by Mar 31 article on long commutes to work, says Rep Vito J Fossella is right to complain about Staten Island's lack of mass transit</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Long and Winding Road, to Work: Many Travel 90 Minutes or More'' (news article, March 31):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Long and Winding Road, to Work: Many Travel 90 Minutes or More'' (news article, March 31):</p>
        <p>United States Representative Vito J. Fossella, a Republican from Staten Island, rightly complains that mass transit for his borough has been neglected.</p>
        <p>He should remind his fellow Republicans that their party has always neglected mass transit. Give tax breaks for the rich and cut back on services for everyone else.</p>
        <p>Robert Watson  Kew Gardens, Queens  March 31, 2005</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
